A typical farm in our D-Block could be said to be{Cobden Farm .Mrs Wright } gave us some details. The farm occupies{95}acres and they have{55} cows.These are dairy cattle for producing milk. Besides the cows there are{260}sheep. The farmer usually sells the bulls and the beef heifers but keeps the dairy heifers. They have two tractors. They put fertilizer on their land between May and June to make the grass grow stronger.
They make silage but they have to make straw for feed and bedding.
On{Cobden Farm}there are no paid farm labourers.They no longer keep pigs because of the time involved.The farm has been in the family for{40}years. {MARK RILEY and JASON WHITFIELD {
